			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">It would be good to have more tests to check that sandbox memory mappings are correct.

 * We have some Windows-only checks for the x86-64 address space guards in mmap_test.c.
 * I'm adding some Windows-only checks for file/SHM mappings and munmap() in mmap_unittest.cc.

We should extend these checks to work on Linux (using /proc/self/maps) and Mac OS X (using Mach syscalls).
